svg.text: The WYNN Literacy Software is very powerful text-to-speech reader. It prides ​itself on a “bimodal” approach. It incorporates highlighting of the text being read ​so that the student can follow along. The product assists students with a vision ​impairment by reading the text on a page to ​them. It also helps students with ADD or ​ADHD by highlighting the text that is ​being read so that the student can focus on ​that one area instead of letting their mind ​wander. In addition, several other features ​address other ​areas like the ​ability to create ​notecards and other writing templates in order to ​enhance comprehension. The software can also be ​paired with a PEARL Camera so that the student can ​place a book under the camera and have it instantly read ​back to him/her. One feature of the software is that it ​will maintain the look and feel of the text. Instead of converting the text to just a ​single block of words, it will maintain the paragraph structure, the columns on a ​page, and even images so that the student is able to see exactly what is being read ​in the same format as if they were to be reading it on paper. Another feature is the ​ability for teachers to lockout certain tools like the dictionary, thesaurus, and ​spell-checking. This way, if the student is taking a test, he/she doesn’t have ​unauthorized access to these tools.​3.What prerequisite skills does a person need in order to use the product/service? ​a.A person using this product would need basic computer skills in order to use ​WYNN. It does seem that great effort was put in to make the user interface ​intuitive, but some of the advance features may require some more advanced ​knowledge of the software.​4.If the product is used in conjunction with a computer, are Windows and Mac versions ​available? Are versions for smart phones and other mobile devices available (e.g. ​Blackberry, iPhone, Android, iPad, other tablets, etc.)? If versions are available for ​different devices, are they essentially the same?​a.WYNN is only available for windows and does not have a mobile version.​5.What qualifications or eligibility criteria, if any, does an individual need to meet in order ​to obtain the product/service (e.g. disability, age/grade level)? What documentation is ​required if there are eligibility criteria?​a.Anyone can use the software.​6.What does the product/service cost?
